Package view

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EndNavigation
    The Navigation bar at the end of the game.
    EndView
    The view at the end of the game.
    EstuaryPopup
    The EstuaryPopup displays the Animal the player must catch next, and a continue button.
    EstuaryView
    Represents the Estuary environment portion of the game
    ObjectView
    ObjectView is an abstract class that is representative of any view that draws GameObjects
    QuizView
    The QuizView represents the screen for the game's quiz.
    ResearchPopup
    The ResearchPopup represents popups that will appear during the research scene.
    ResearchView
    The view for the Research screen
    TextPanel
    The panel used to display text at the end of the game on the EndView
    TimerImage
    Class for creation of the circular TimerImage
    TitleNavigation
    The pane at the bottom of the Title Screen for starting the game, exiting, or loading in the tutorial.
    TitleView
    The View representing the Title Screen of the game.
    TutorialPopup
    The TutorialPopup class represents popups that will appear during the Tutorial.
    View
    This is the abstract View class which all the views extend, this includes attributes that every view must have like dimmensions, time, GameObjects, and a CodeListener.
    ViewContainer
    The ViewContainer contains the JFrame for the game and uses panes to switch from view to view without having to open multiple windows during the running of the game.
